sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant RequestingNode as Requesting Federation Node
    participant FederationApi as Federation API Endpoint
    participant TrustLayer as Security Layer 1: Trust Boundary Check
    participant ReplayLayer as Security Layer 2: Replay Protection Check
    participant SignatureLayer as Security Layer 3: Signature Integrity Check
    participant SecurityDatabase as SQLite Security Database
    participant FederationCoordinator as Federation Coordination Service
    participant EpochLayer as Security Layer 4: Epoch and Threshold Check
    participant LuksMountLayer as Security Layer 5: Encrypted Mount Check
    participant SecureFileApi as Secure File Access API

    RequestingNode->>FederationApi: Submit payload with node_id, nonce, timestamp, signature, shard

    FederationApi->>TrustLayer: Run trust boundary validation
    alt Layer 1 PASS (sender trusted and no transitive fields)
        rect rgba(221, 255, 227, 0.7)
            Note over TrustLayer,FederationApi: PASS PATH - Trust check succeeded
            TrustLayer-->>FederationApi: Pass
        end
    else Layer 1 REJECT
        rect rgba(255, 224, 224, 0.7)
            Note over TrustLayer,SecurityDatabase: REJECT PATH - Trust boundary violation
            TrustLayer->>SecurityDatabase: Write trust rejection audit reason
            FederationApi-->>RequestingNode: HTTP 403 Rejected at Trust Layer
        end
    end

    FederationApi->>ReplayLayer: Run timestamp skew and nonce uniqueness checks
    alt Layer 2 PASS (fresh timestamp and new nonce)
        rect rgba(221, 255, 227, 0.7)
            Note over ReplayLayer,SecurityDatabase: PASS PATH - Fresh timestamp and unique nonce
            ReplayLayer->>SecurityDatabase: Store consumed nonce
            ReplayLayer-->>FederationApi: Pass
        end
    else Layer 2 REJECT
        rect rgba(255, 224, 224, 0.7)
            Note over ReplayLayer,SecurityDatabase: REJECT PATH - Replay or stale timestamp
            ReplayLayer->>SecurityDatabase: Write replay rejection audit reason
            FederationApi-->>RequestingNode: HTTP 400 or 409 Rejected at Replay Layer
        end
    end

    FederationApi->>SignatureLayer: Recompute canonical HMAC and compare constant-time
    alt Layer 3 PASS (signature valid)
        rect rgba(221, 255, 227, 0.7)
            Note over SignatureLayer,SecurityDatabase: PASS PATH - Signature verified
            SignatureLayer->>SecurityDatabase: Write signature pass audit entry
            SignatureLayer-->>FederationApi: Pass
        end
    else Layer 3 REJECT
        rect rgba(255, 224, 224, 0.7)
            Note over SignatureLayer,SecurityDatabase: REJECT PATH - Invalid signature
            SignatureLayer->>SecurityDatabase: Write signature rejection audit reason
            FederationApi-->>RequestingNode: HTTP 401 Rejected at Signature Layer
        end
    end

    FederationApi->>FederationCoordinator: Accept shard and continue processing
    FederationCoordinator->>EpochLayer: Validate current epoch and threshold readiness
    alt Layer 4 PASS (valid epoch and threshold met)
        rect rgba(221, 255, 227, 0.7)
            Note over EpochLayer,FederationCoordinator: PASS PATH - Epoch and threshold valid
            EpochLayer-->>FederationCoordinator: Pass
        end
    else Layer 4 REJECT
        rect rgba(255, 224, 224, 0.7)
            Note over EpochLayer,SecurityDatabase: REJECT PATH - Epoch invalid or threshold not met
            EpochLayer->>SecurityDatabase: Write epoch or threshold rejection reason
            FederationCoordinator-->>FederationApi: Stop reconstruction
            FederationApi-->>RequestingNode: HTTP 202 Accepted shard, waiting or invalid epoch state
        end
    end

    FederationCoordinator->>LuksMountLayer: Reconstruct key and attempt encrypted mount
    alt Layer 5 PASS (mount active)
        rect rgba(221, 255, 227, 0.7)
            Note over LuksMountLayer,FederationCoordinator: PASS PATH - Secure volume mounted
            LuksMountLayer-->>FederationCoordinator: Pass
            FederationCoordinator-->>FederationApi: Secure storage ready
            FederationApi-->>RequestingNode: HTTP 200 Accepted and Ready
        end
    else Layer 5 REJECT
        rect rgba(255, 224, 224, 0.7)
            Note over LuksMountLayer,SecurityDatabase: REJECT PATH - Mount failed or fallback active
            LuksMountLayer->>SecurityDatabase: Write mount failure audit reason
            FederationCoordinator-->>FederationApi: Degraded mode or fallback
            FederationApi-->>RequestingNode: HTTP 202 Accepted but Mount Not Ready
        end
    end

    SecureFileApi->>LuksMountLayer: Verify mounted state before listing or download
    alt File Access PASS
        rect rgba(221, 255, 227, 0.7)
            SecureFileApi-->>RequestingNode: Return secure files
        end
    else File Access REJECT
        rect rgba(255, 224, 224, 0.7)
            SecureFileApi-->>RequestingNode: Deny secure file access
        end
    end